President Biden spoke with Prime Minister Netanyahu of Israel to express his sympathy for the victims of the Hamas terrorist assault and pledged his support to the government and people of Israel. They discussed the taking of hostages, including families, the elderly, and children, and emphasized that there is no justification for terrorism. President Biden updated the Prime Minister on the United States' diplomatic engagement in support of Israel and conveyed that additional assistance for the Israeli Defense Forces is on its way. They also discussed efforts to ensure that no enemies of Israel take advantage of the situation and committed to staying in regular contact.